Determine the values of `total` and `k` after the following code executes:

```java
int total = 0;
int k = 12;
while (k > 0) {
    total += k;
    k -= 4;
}
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
int count = 0;
for (int n = 1; n <= 20; n++) {
    if (n % 3 == 0) {
        count++;
    }
}
System.out.println(count);
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
int sum = 7;
int count = 2;
double avg = sum / count;
System.out.println(avg);
```

The following code is intended to find the minimum value among positive multiples of 4 up to 20. What does it actually print?

```java
int min = 0;
for (int i = 4; i <= 20; i += 4) {
    if (i < min) {
        min = i;
    }
}
System.out.println(min);
```

Which variable in the following code segment serves as the accumulator?

```java
int n = 1;
int result = 0;
while (n <= 10) {
    result += n * n;
    n++;
}
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
int a = 0;
int b = 10;
while (a < b) {
    a += 2;
    b -= 1;
}
System.out.println(a + " " + b);
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
int n = 352;
int sum = 0;
while (n > 0) {
    sum += n % 10;
    n /= 10;
}
System.out.println(sum);
```

Determine the value of `max` after the following code executes:

```java
int max = 0;
for (int i = 2; i <= 8; i += 2) {
    if (i * i > max) {
        max = i * i;
    }
}
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
int evens = 0;
int odds = 0;
for (int i = 1; i <= 9; i++) {
    if (i % 2 == 0) {
        evens++;
    } else {
        odds++;
    }
}
System.out.println(evens + " " + odds);
```

The following code is intended to count integers from 1 to 100 that are divisible by both 3 and 5. Which change would correct the bug?

```java
int count = 0;
for (int i = 1; i <= 100; i++) {
    if (i % 3 == 0 || i % 5 == 0) {
        count++;
    }
}
System.out.println(count);
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
int sum = 0;
for (int k = 1; k <= 4; k++) {
    sum += k * 2;
}
System.out.println(sum);
```

What is the value of `count` after the following code executes?

```java
int count = 0;
for (int i = 10; i <= 30; i += 5) {
    if (i % 3 == 0) {
        count++;
    }
}
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
int total = 0;
int count = 0;
int val = 1;
while (val <= 4) {
    total += val;
    count++;
    val++;
}
double avg = total / count;
System.out.println(avg);
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
int max = 0;
int n = 293;
while (n > 0) {
    int digit = n % 10;
    if (digit > max) {
        max = digit;
    }
    n /= 10;
}
System.out.println(max);
```

The code below is intended to find and print the smallest of five positive integers. Which of the following best describes the error?

```java
int a = 7, b = 3, c = 9, d = 1, e = 5;
int min = 0;
if (a < min) min = a;
if (b < min) min = b;
if (c < min) min = c;
if (d < min) min = d;
if (e < min) min = e;
System.out.println(min);
```

