while (n > 0) {
    sum += n % 10;
    n /= 10;
}
```

What is the value of `min` after the following code executes?

```java
int min = 1000;
for (int i = 1; i <= 4; i++) {
    int val = i * i - 5 * i + 7;
    if (val < min) {
        min = val;
    }
}
```

Which of the following best describes the role of the variable `total` in the code below?

```java
int total = 0;
for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
    total += i;
}
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
int n = 4805;
int count = 0;
int sum = 0;

while (n > 0)
{
    int digit = n % 10;
    if (digit % 2 == 0)
    {
        count++;
        sum += digit;
    }
    n /= 10;
}

System.out.print(count + " " + sum);
```

Determine the values of `total`, `count`, and `avg` after the following code runs.

```java
int total = 0;
int count = 0;

for (int i = 1; i <= 8; i++)
{
    if (i % 3 != 0)
    {
        total += i;
        count++;
    }
}

double avg = (double) total / count;
```
